The course introduces a selection of contemporary social problems that affect people's well-being and the functioning of society.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at -	introducing  contemporary social problems and theoretical and empirical approaches to these problems; -	introducing methods of studying social problems of contemporary societies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successfully completing the course, a student  (1)	knows a selection of theoretical and empirical approaches describing and explaining contemporary social problems;  (2)	knows a selection of methods for studying social problems of contemporary societies;  (3)	is able to describe and analyse some contemporary social problems based on academic sources.
